In SNF, the edge weight matrix W is converted into a full kernel normalized weight matrix P = D−1W, where D is the diagonal matrix whose entries D(i, j) = ΣjW(i, j). The local affinity S is measured using K nearest neighbors on the weight matrix W. For the given two similarity matrices in a general SNF setting, an important step is to iteratively update the matrix corresponding to each of the affinity matrices as in equation (6).6\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
